Text.SourceString: What do you want?//I’ve got no business with you.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you want?//I’ve got no business with you.

Text.SourceString: Are you always this chatty?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you always this chatty?

Text.SourceString: People sure like to garden here. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: People sure like to garden here. Tch.

Text.SourceString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could.

Text.SourceString: Lots of people here, like my sister, grow their own food.//There’s a small garden in front of the guild too… It’s <NpcName>Kira</>'s.
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of people here, like my sister, grow their own food.//There’s a small garden in front of the guild too… It’s <NpcName>Kira</>'s.

Text.SourceString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could. But it wouldn’t be safe for them.//They don’t know how to live in the wild.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could. But it wouldn’t be safe for them.//They don’t know how to live in the wild.

Text.SourceString: I don’t go to the cavern.//I don’t have any reason to since I don’t mine or collect artifacts.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t go to the cavern.//I don’t have any reason to since I don’t mine or collect artifacts.

Text.SourceString: So, you came here from Pokyo, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: So, you came here from Pokyo, huh?

Text.SourceString: Pokyo has a real problem with strays. Their shelters are overcrowded.
Text.LocalizedString: Pokyo has a real problem with strays. Their shelters are overcrowded.

Text.SourceString: What are you doing here on a Thursday?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you doing here on a Thursday?

Text.SourceString: Can you believe this heat? I’ve never sweat so much in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe this heat? I’ve never sweat so much in my life.

Text.SourceString: People here seem to like Spring weather.//They’re so annoyingly vocal about it.
Text.LocalizedString: People here seem to like Spring weather.//They’re so annoyingly vocal about it.

Text.SourceString: I could use some homemade tomato soup.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use some homemade tomato soup.

Text.SourceString: Kinda nice to see you out in this harsh weather.//<portrait=normal>Doesn’t seem like it bothers you, huh?//Nice, nice.
Text.LocalizedString: Kinda nice to see you out in this harsh weather.//<portrait=normal>Doesn’t seem like it bothers you, huh?//Nice, nice.

Text.SourceString: The birds are back.
Text.LocalizedString: The birds are back.

Text.SourceString: The birds are back.//It’s nice to walk outside with them around again.
Text.LocalizedString: The birds are back.//It’s nice to walk outside with them around again.

Text.SourceString: It would be better if it were Winter all year round. Maybe I should move farther north.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be better if it were Winter all year round. Maybe I should move farther north.

Text.SourceString: Need to put out more water for the animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Need to put out more water for the animals.

Text.SourceString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>No, it isn’t. Stop complaining.
Text.LocalizedString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>No, it isn’t. Stop complaining.

Text.SourceString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>Maybe it’s a bit hot, but nothing unbearable.
Text.LocalizedString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>Maybe it’s a bit hot, but nothing unbearable.

Text.SourceString: Breathe that Winter air in, Garden Rake.//It’ll toughen you up.
Text.LocalizedString: Breathe that Winter air in, Garden Rake.//It’ll toughen you up.

Text.SourceString: Breathe that Winter air in, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It’ll toughen you up.
Text.LocalizedString: Breathe that Winter air in, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It’ll toughen you up.

Text.SourceString: I don’t have any weapons at home, no. Why?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have any weapons at home, no. Why?

Text.SourceString: I don’t have any weapons at home, no.//I have a niece living with me, <NPCName>Zoe</>. I don’t want any accidents or anything like that.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have any weapons at home, no.//I have a niece living with me, <NPCName>Zoe</>. I don’t want any accidents or anything like that.

Text.SourceString: Caught someone slipping in the rain the other day…wearing sandals. Tch.//And he wondered why he slipped.
Text.LocalizedString: Caught someone slipping in the rain the other day…wearing sandals. Tch.//And he wondered why he slipped.

Text.SourceString: You need a pair of nice sturdy boots for walking in the rain.//My boots have saved me from slipping many times.
Text.LocalizedString: You need a pair of nice sturdy boots for walking in the rain.//My boots have saved me from slipping many times.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like fishing.//And I also don’t like being interrupted.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like fishing.//And I also don’t like being interrupted.

Text.SourceString: Fishing isn’t my thing. I could if I had to, of course.//<portrait=annoyed>What type of person couldn’t fish or make their own food?
Text.LocalizedString: Fishing isn’t my thing. I could if I had to, of course.//<portrait=annoyed>What type of person couldn’t fish or make their own food?

Text.SourceString: The hot spring is free. I wonder why more people don’t go there.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring is free. I wonder why more people don’t go there.

Text.SourceString: It’s safe here in Fall. It isn’t too hot.//In some places, this is wildfire season.//I’ve run away from several of those myself.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s safe here in Fall. It isn’t too hot.//In some places, this is wildfire season.//I’ve run away from several of those myself.

Text.SourceString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same.

Text.SourceString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same. We make too much fuss about them.//The temperature changes. No big deal.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same. We make too much fuss about them.//The temperature changes. No big deal.

Text.SourceString: Why are you talking to me here in the rain?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you talking to me here in the rain?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?

Text.SourceString: Why are you talking to me here in a storm?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you talking to me here in a storm?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?

Text.SourceString: Why are you still here?
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you still here?

Text.SourceString: Stop looking at my face. It’s still the same. Nothing’s changed.
Text.LocalizedString: Stop looking at my face. It’s still the same. Nothing’s changed.

Text.SourceString: The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=angry>Any other questions?
Text.LocalizedString: The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=angry>Any other questions?

Text.SourceString: The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=normal>Do you think I’d be less miserable if I’d never gotten attacked?//I don’t think so.
Text.LocalizedString: The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=normal>Do you think I’d be less miserable if I’d never gotten attacked?//I don’t think so.

Text.SourceString: You’re adventurous, aren’t you, Garden Rake?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re adventurous, aren’t you, Garden Rake?

Text.SourceString: What? You don’t like the nickname?
Text.LocalizedString: What? You don’t like the nickname?

Text.SourceString: Heh heh!//[His chuckles sound like an earthquake.]
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh!//[His chuckles sound like an earthquake.]

Text.SourceString: Ha! Easy on the compliments. We just met. You don’t really know me yet.//<portrait=annoyed>Easily impressed, are you?
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! Easy on the compliments. We just met. You don’t really know me yet.//<portrait=annoyed>Easily impressed, are you?

Text.SourceString: Sorry if I call you Garden Rake. It’s a reference to the first time we– Tch. Never mind.//<portrait=angry>If you don’t like the nickname, that’s too bad, ’cause it’ll stick.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if I call you Garden Rake. It’s a reference to the first time we– Tch. Never mind.//<portrait=angry>If you don’t like the nickname, that’s too bad, ’cause it’ll stick.

Text.SourceString: Those monsters were sure agitated today.//Eavesdropping on me, Garden Rake?
Text.LocalizedString: Those monsters were sure agitated today.//Eavesdropping on me, Garden Rake?

Text.SourceString: No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.

Text.SourceString: Watch out if you’re headed into the cavern today. <Italic>They</> seem agitated.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out if you’re headed into the cavern today. <Italic>They</> seem agitated.

Text.SourceString: No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.//I have important things to do.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.//I have important things to do.

Text.SourceString: Your hair is wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Your hair is wet.

Text.SourceString: Your hair is wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Your hair is wet.

Text.SourceString: You look like you’re about to give me opinions.//What is it? Spit it out.
Text.LocalizedString: You look like you’re about to give me opinions.//What is it? Spit it out.

Text.SourceString: Right, the big old scar.
Text.LocalizedString: Right, the big old scar.

Text.SourceString: Jeez! I wouldn’t have known if you hadn’t mentioned it. Thanks, Sherlock.
Text.LocalizedString: Jeez! I wouldn’t have known if you hadn’t mentioned it. Thanks, Sherlock.

Special.SourceString: You have a giant scar across your face.
Special.LocalizedString: You have a giant scar across your face.

Text.SourceString: Ha!//<portrait=angry>Flirting, are you, Garden Rake?//<portrait=annoyed>Thanks. Scars are sexy. That’s why I have one.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha!//<portrait=angry>Flirting, are you, Garden Rake?//<portrait=annoyed>Thanks. Scars are sexy. That’s why I have one.

Special.SourceString: That scar looks good on you.
Special.LocalizedString: That scar looks good on you.

Text.SourceString: I got my scar from one of the cats at the shelter. Not from fighting off a bear or a wolf, not from combat. Nope!//<portrait=annoyed>I’m far too good to get injured in combat. Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>It’s the one you let your guard down for who hurts you.
Text.LocalizedString: I got my scar from one of the cats at the shelter. Not from fighting off a bear or a wolf, not from combat. Nope!//<portrait=annoyed>I’m far too good to get injured in combat. Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>It’s the one you let your guard down for who hurts you.

Text.SourceString: My scar might look scary to people, but I’m not too worried about it.//My face is fine. Still functioning as intended.
Text.LocalizedString: My scar might look scary to people, but I’m not too worried about it.//My face is fine. Still functioning as intended.

Text.SourceString: Poor Chap, the cat that scratched me, didn’t mean it.// I was about to give him his vaccine, and he was scared. But he was very brave about it at the end of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Poor Chap, the cat that scratched me, didn’t mean it.// I was about to give him his vaccine, and he was scared. But he was very brave about it at the end of the day.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like talking about my scar because first of all, it’s nobody’s business.//<portrait=angry>Second of all, it’s <Italic>still</> nobody’s business.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like talking about my scar because first of all, it’s nobody’s business.//<portrait=angry>Second of all, it’s <Italic>still</> nobody’s business.

Text.SourceString: I don’t live here. This is where I work.//<portrait=angry>Those aren’t my crops. I look like a farmer to ya?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t live here. This is where I work.//<portrait=angry>Those aren’t my crops. I look like a farmer to ya?

Text.SourceString: I love the cold. Mmm…invigorating!
Text.LocalizedString: I love the cold. Mmm…invigorating!

Text.SourceString: I’ve never stepped foot into Socket Electronics in my life.//<portrait=annoyed>Socket & Pan – yeah, whatever. The electronics store.//I don’t have much use for gadgets.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve never stepped foot into Socket Electronics in my life.//<portrait=annoyed>Socket & Pan – yeah, whatever. The electronics store.//I don’t have much use for gadgets.

Text.SourceString: Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here.
Text.LocalizedString: Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here.

Text.SourceString: Name’s Funbucket.
Text.LocalizedString: Name’s Funbucket.

Text.SourceString: Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here.//<portrait=happy>It was adorable.
Text.LocalizedString: Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here.//<portrait=happy>It was adorable.

Text.SourceString: I spoke to <NpcName>Ben</> some time ago. Saw him walking the duck near the cavern. He told me his name was Funbucket.//<portrait=angry>And by “his” I mean the duck’s name, not <NpcName>Ben’s</>. <NpcName>Ben’s</> name is Ben.
Text.LocalizedString: I spoke to <NpcName>Ben</> some time ago. Saw him walking the duck near the cavern. He told me his name was Funbucket.//<portrait=angry>And by “his” I mean the duck’s name, not <NpcName>Ben’s</>. <NpcName>Ben’s</> name is Ben.

Text.SourceString: It’s quiet tonight, just how I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s quiet tonight, just how I like it.

Text.SourceString: It’s quiet tonight. A little too quiet.//Stay frosty, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s quiet tonight. A little too quiet.//Stay frosty, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m visiting <NPCName>Rafael</> later today.//My sword could use some sharpening.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m visiting <NPCName>Rafael</> later today.//My sword could use some sharpening.

Text.SourceString: Gah, it’s Winter. Means he’s busy upgrading farming tools.//<portrait=normal>I’ll wait till Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah, it’s Winter. Means he’s busy upgrading farming tools.//<portrait=normal>I’ll wait till Spring.

Text.SourceString: You’re walking around at this time of day like you got nothing to do.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re walking around at this time of day like you got nothing to do.

Text.SourceString: I’m a little tired today. <NPCName>Paul</> thought he saw the wooded bighorn in the backyard last night, and…//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was a whole thing. No one got much sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a little tired today. <NPCName>Paul</> thought he saw the wooded bighorn in the backyard last night, and…//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was a whole thing. No one got much sleep.

Text.SourceString: I like the hot cocoa from the Coffee Corner.//Don’t like coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the hot cocoa from the Coffee Corner.//Don’t like coffee.

Text.SourceString: My favorite thing to get from the Coffee Corner is hot cocoa.//Not a fan of coffee. It’s a tad bitter for my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite thing to get from the Coffee Corner is hot cocoa.//Not a fan of coffee. It’s a tad bitter for my taste.

Text.SourceString: I’m sick of hearing people whine about how they can’t handle a little bit of cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sick of hearing people whine about how they can’t handle a little bit of cold weather.

Text.SourceString: My dog likes to hang around here.//He’s probably napping somewhere by the clinic right now if he isn’t playing with the kids at school.
Text.LocalizedString: My dog likes to hang around here.//He’s probably napping somewhere by the clinic right now if he isn’t playing with the kids at school.

Text.SourceString: This job at the animal shelter doesn’t pay much.
Text.LocalizedString: This job at the animal shelter doesn’t pay much.

Text.SourceString: Good thing making a lot of money doesn’t interest me.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing making a lot of money doesn’t interest me.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to take care of the shelter.//<portrait=angry>What? Pick up a broom. Help out.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to take care of the shelter.//<portrait=angry>What? Pick up a broom. Help out.

Text.SourceString: Gotta make sure the shelter is clean and safe for the animals.//They don’t have anywhere else to go.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta make sure the shelter is clean and safe for the animals.//They don’t have anywhere else to go.

Text.SourceString: Some of the animals at the shelter just wandered here from Hillside or the forest. Like Taco, the vineyard’s dog.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the animals at the shelter just wandered here from Hillside or the forest. Like Taco, the vineyard’s dog.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for an animal?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for an animal?

Text.SourceString: I need to clean all the litter boxes today.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to clean all the litter boxes today.

Text.SourceString: It gets busy in here on the weekend.//There’s a yoga class on Saturdays.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets busy in here on the weekend.//There’s a yoga class on Saturdays.

Text.SourceString: Me? No, thanks. I don’t think I’ll be joining the yoga class anytime soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? No, thanks. I don’t think I’ll be joining the yoga class anytime soon.

Text.SourceString: You’re not looking for seeds here, are you?//<portrait=angry>I don’t sell seeds.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not looking for seeds here, are you?//<portrait=angry>I don’t sell seeds.

Text.SourceString: If you’re going to keep talking, let me go first…
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re going to keep talking, let me go first…

Text.SourceString: Why do you look like that? I startled you, huh? Tch.//<portrait=normal>Jumpy farmer, aren’t ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Why do you look like that? I startled you, huh? Tch.//<portrait=normal>Jumpy farmer, aren’t ya?

Text.SourceString: Summer’s almost here.//Might need to change up my gear.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer’s almost here.//Might need to change up my gear.

Text.SourceString: I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.

Text.SourceString: You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.
Text.LocalizedString: You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.

Text.SourceString: I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.//You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.//You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.

Text.SourceString: That would require you to be <Italic>able</> to fish in the first place.
Text.LocalizedString: That would require you to be <Italic>able</> to fish in the first place.

Text.SourceString: All the weapons are in the guild, not here.
Text.LocalizedString: All the weapons are in the guild, not here.

Text.SourceString: We keep weapons in the B.O.S. guild right there. That little round door by the bush.//It’s safer to keep them all in one place. Easier to maintain too.
Text.LocalizedString: We keep weapons in the B.O.S. guild right there. That little round door by the bush.//It’s safer to keep them all in one place. Easier to maintain too.

Text.SourceString: You have animals on your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: You have animals on your farm?

Text.SourceString: You feed them all right over there? Let them get some sun sometimes?
Text.LocalizedString: You feed them all right over there? Let them get some sun sometimes?

Text.SourceString: Those rotten roots on the beach are nasty.//I tried getting rid of them over there. Cutting them up doesn’t work.
Text.LocalizedString: Those rotten roots on the beach are nasty.//I tried getting rid of them over there. Cutting them up doesn’t work.

Text.SourceString: They come back again.//I think the solution might be down on the ocean bed.
Text.LocalizedString: They come back again.//I think the solution might be down on the ocean bed.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and hot today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and hot today.

Text.SourceString: I like reading books at the beach.//<portrait=angry>I don’t care if people think it’s a cliché.
Text.LocalizedString: I like reading books at the beach.//<portrait=angry>I don’t care if people think it’s a cliché.

Text.SourceString: Not surprising to see you at the beach in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Not surprising to see you at the beach in Summer.

Text.SourceString: I’m certainly gonna spend my Summer at the beach. Why not?//<portrait=normal>It’s free. It’s fun.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m certainly gonna spend my Summer at the beach. Why not?//<portrait=normal>It’s free. It’s fun.

Text.SourceString: Hot spring is empty this time of year.//Perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot spring is empty this time of year.//Perfect.

Text.SourceString: Weird that shiitake only grow here in Spring.//They grow in Spring and Fall in Beluga.
Text.LocalizedString: Weird that shiitake only grow here in Spring.//They grow in Spring and Fall in Beluga.

Text.SourceString: The sunscreen they sell around here comes in tiny little bottles.//It barely covers my legs. Tch.//<portrait=angry>What a scam!
Text.LocalizedString: The sunscreen they sell around here comes in tiny little bottles.//It barely covers my legs. Tch.//<portrait=angry>What a scam!

Text.SourceString: Here I thought I was gonna read my book in peace. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: Here I thought I was gonna read my book in peace. Tch.

Text.SourceString: Don’t pass out. The shack sells coconuts.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t pass out. The shack sells coconuts.

Text.SourceString: The ones on the trees aren’t ripe yet. Could be wrong…
Text.LocalizedString: The ones on the trees aren’t ripe yet. Could be wrong…

Text.SourceString: Hey! Can’t resist the beach in this weather either, huh?//<portrait=happy>Look at us. The moment the sun shines, we hit the beach. Typical islanders. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey! Can’t resist the beach in this weather either, huh?//<portrait=happy>Look at us. The moment the sun shines, we hit the beach. Typical islanders. Tch.

Text.SourceString: This book is from the library.
Text.LocalizedString: This book is from the library.

Text.SourceString: I don’t buy books. I prefer to read the free ones.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t buy books. I prefer to read the free ones.

Text.SourceString: There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – hardly see anybody around.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – hardly see anybody around.

Text.SourceString: When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.
Text.LocalizedString: When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling a little sore from training the other day.//<portrait=sad>At least now I’m relaxing here on the beach, but it doesn’t seem to help my muscle recovery.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling a little sore from training the other day.//<portrait=sad>At least now I’m relaxing here on the beach, but it doesn’t seem to help my muscle recovery.

Text.SourceString: I might need to hit the hot spring on the way home. Just a dip or something.//<portrait=annoyed>This heat? Tch. Doesn’t bother me.
Text.LocalizedString: I might need to hit the hot spring on the way home. Just a dip or something.//<portrait=annoyed>This heat? Tch. Doesn’t bother me.

Text.SourceString: You’re in my way.//I need to see if the shiitake are sprouting yet.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re in my way.//I need to see if the shiitake are sprouting yet.

Text.SourceString: Shiitake are great. Other mushrooms are okay.//Not that good.
Text.LocalizedString: Shiitake are great. Other mushrooms are okay.//Not that good.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna be here for a bit.//<portrait=annoyed>Why are you still here?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna be here for a bit.//<portrait=annoyed>Why are you still here?

Text.SourceString: Didn’t bring anything to eat today. I thought I could just pop by the shack if I get hungry.//It’s right there.//<portrait=annoyed>I did get some coffee this morning. Bad decision. Should’ve gotten the hot cocoa instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Didn’t bring anything to eat today. I thought I could just pop by the shack if I get hungry.//It’s right there.//<portrait=annoyed>I did get some coffee this morning. Bad decision. Should’ve gotten the hot cocoa instead.

Text.SourceString: Here for those yoga classes, are ya?//Pink Hair teaches it. See it all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: Here for those yoga classes, are ya?//Pink Hair teaches it. See it all the time.

Text.SourceString: There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – hardly see anybody around.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – hardly see anybody around.

Text.SourceString: When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.
Text.LocalizedString: When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.

Text.SourceString: You sure are everywhere, Garden Rake.//<portrait=normal>All right, what is it?
Text.LocalizedString: You sure are everywhere, Garden Rake.//<portrait=normal>All right, what is it?

Text.SourceString: The hot water feels good.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot water feels good.

Text.SourceString: I can feel my muscles relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: I can feel my muscles relaxing.

Text.SourceString: This place is free.
Text.LocalizedString: This place is free.

Text.SourceString: Heard you had something to do with getting it going again. Is that right?
Text.LocalizedString: Heard you had something to do with getting it going again. Is that right?

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna see if there’s some mushrooms out there. After this. Aaaaah…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna see if there’s some mushrooms out there. After this. Aaaaah…

Text.SourceString: You know, it’s amazing how you manage to keep all those plants alive when you can barely take care of yourself. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, it’s amazing how you manage to keep all those plants alive when you can barely take care of yourself. Tch.

Text.SourceString: You know, I have to say you’re not as completely useless as I thought.//<portrait=normal>Maybe there’s hope for you yet, Garden Rake.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I have to say you’re not as completely useless as I thought.//<portrait=normal>Maybe there’s hope for you yet, Garden Rake.

Text.SourceString: I’m liking this part of the forest way more than the woodland.//<portrait=angry>There are more bugs here, though. Annoying.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m liking this part of the forest way more than the woodland.//<portrait=angry>There are more bugs here, though. Annoying.

Text.SourceString: Training day for me today.//<portrait=annoyed>You got nothing better to do?
Text.LocalizedString: Training day for me today.//<portrait=annoyed>You got nothing better to do?

Text.SourceString: Watch your step.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step.

Text.SourceString: Nice day, huh?//I like the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice day, huh?//I like the rain.

Text.SourceString: Nice day, huh?//I like the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice day, huh?//I like the snow.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there. It’s icy.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there. It’s icy.

Text.SourceString: You look pretty good when you’re all covered in dirt from working on the farm.//It suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look pretty good when you’re all covered in dirt from working on the farm.//It suits you.

Text.SourceString: If you ever need a break from the farm, I wouldn’t mind showing you some of the more secluded spots in the forest…or at sea.//<portrait=normal>You seem like the swimming type.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever need a break from the farm, I wouldn’t mind showing you some of the more secluded spots in the forest…or at sea.//<portrait=normal>You seem like the swimming type.

Text.SourceString: If we ever get tired of our usual roles, maybe I could take care of the animals, and you could…take care of me?
Text.LocalizedString: If we ever get tired of our usual roles, maybe I could take care of the animals, and you could…take care of me?

Text.SourceString: Looking good, Garden Rake.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking good, Garden Rake.

Text.SourceString: You’ve got charm, I admit.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve got charm, I admit.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne’s</> been busy lately, but she always makes sure we have a good meal. Can’t complain.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne’s</> been busy lately, but she always makes sure we have a good meal. Can’t complain.

Text.SourceString: She’s a good sister. I need to cut her some slack.//<portrait=angry>She gets too nosy about Mom sometimes. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s a good sister. I need to cut her some slack.//<portrait=angry>She gets too nosy about Mom sometimes. Tch.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy.//Dude’s solid. I like him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy.//Dude’s solid. I like him.

Text.SourceString: He could tackle a bear if he wanted to. He can protect my niece fine.
Text.LocalizedString: He could tackle a bear if he wanted to. He can protect my niece fine.

Text.SourceString: My niece will grow up to be a great hunter. She’s sharp.
Text.LocalizedString: My niece will grow up to be a great hunter. She’s sharp.

Text.SourceString: I’ll teach her everything I know.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll teach her everything I know.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like kids.//I only like my niece.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like kids.//I only like my niece.

Text.SourceString: They’re all so loud. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re all so loud. Tch.

Text.SourceString: The curly brown dog you see around town is mine. Well, <Italic>ours</>, I guess.//Bonbon is <NpcName>Zoe’s</>.
Text.LocalizedString: The curly brown dog you see around town is mine. Well, <Italic>ours</>, I guess.//Bonbon is <NpcName>Zoe’s</>.

Text.SourceString: Bonbon and <NpcName>Zoe</> are probably the same age.//<portrait=happy>The lil guy looks like a puppy, though, huh?//Acts like one too.
Text.LocalizedString: Bonbon and <NpcName>Zoe</> are probably the same age.//<portrait=happy>The lil guy looks like a puppy, though, huh?//Acts like one too.

Text.SourceString: I need to write back to my mom.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to write back to my mom.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne’s</> been bugging me about it all Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne’s</> been bugging me about it all Winter.

Text.SourceString: This is a nice spot.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a nice spot.

Text.SourceString: You ever try egg custard? It’s like a hug for your taste buds.//<portrait=annoyed>But hey, maybe that’s too fancy for a farmer.//<portrait=happy>Teasing. Don’t be mad <Italic>please</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You ever try egg custard? It’s like a hug for your taste buds.//<portrait=annoyed>But hey, maybe that’s too fancy for a farmer.//<portrait=happy>Teasing. Don’t be mad <Italic>please</>.

Text.SourceString: You’re the fanciest and the <Italic>only</> farmer I know.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re the fanciest and the <Italic>only</> farmer I know.

Text.SourceString: Hot peppers? Why would anyone willingly set their mouth on fire? No, thank you.//Not a chance.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot peppers? Why would anyone willingly set their mouth on fire? No, thank you.//Not a chance.

Text.SourceString: Goat cheese – the bane of my existence.//Can’t fathom how anyone can eat that stuff without gagging.
Text.LocalizedString: Goat cheese – the bane of my existence.//Can’t fathom how anyone can eat that stuff without gagging.

Text.SourceString: Shiitake’s in season, right? Good stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Shiitake’s in season, right? Good stuff.

Text.SourceString: Snow’s beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow’s beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Snow’s beautiful…like you.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow’s beautiful…like you.

Text.SourceString: Layer up, Garden Rake. Winter’s not kind to the unprepared.
Text.LocalizedString: Layer up, Garden Rake. Winter’s not kind to the unprepared.

Text.SourceString: The animals in the shelter need extra care in this cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The animals in the shelter need extra care in this cold weather.

Text.SourceString: I saw some kids flying kites the other day. Pretty cute, actually.//<portrait=happy>Maybe kids aren’t so bad.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw some kids flying kites the other day. Pretty cute, actually.//<portrait=happy>Maybe kids aren’t so bad.

Text.SourceString: The scarf? It’s <NpcName>Anne</>'s. Why? Does it look weird? It’s warm.
Text.LocalizedString: The scarf? It’s <NpcName>Anne</>'s. Why? Does it look weird? It’s warm.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna spend money on new scarves. It’s wasteful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna spend money on new scarves. It’s wasteful.

Text.SourceString: It’s harvest time, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Better make the most of it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s harvest time, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Better make the most of it.

Text.SourceString: The animals in the shelter need extra water in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The animals in the shelter need extra water in this weather.

Text.SourceString: It could be 100 degrees out, but I’m never wearing sandals. I don’t care.//Gotta protect my feet.
Text.LocalizedString: It could be 100 degrees out, but I’m never wearing sandals. I don’t care.//Gotta protect my feet.

Text.SourceString: Boots are the way to go – sturdy and reliable.
Text.LocalizedString: Boots are the way to go – sturdy and reliable.

Text.SourceString: Gardening in Spring can be pretty rewarding.//Teaching my niece that.
Text.LocalizedString: Gardening in Spring can be pretty rewarding.//Teaching my niece that.

Text.SourceString: Our neighbor’s got some garden too.//<portrait=annoyed>Wildlife came along and trashed it pretty good. They blamed <NpcName>Paul</> for it. Tch.
Text.LocalizedString: Our neighbor’s got some garden too.//<portrait=annoyed>Wildlife came along and trashed it pretty good. They blamed <NpcName>Paul</> for it. Tch.

Text.SourceString: They were pretty ticked off at <NpcName>Paul</> since we have those wildlife feeders near the house.//<portrait=normal>They asked him to close them at night to avoid attracting critters to the neighborhood.
Text.LocalizedString: They were pretty ticked off at <NpcName>Paul</> since we have those wildlife feeders near the house.//<portrait=normal>They asked him to close them at night to avoid attracting critters to the neighborhood.

Text.SourceString: If you ever need any help with farmwork, just ask.//Not that I’m volunteering, but you know. I’m around.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever need any help with farmwork, just ask.//Not that I’m volunteering, but you know. I’m around.

Text.SourceString: Keep an eye out for wild mushrooms.//They can be a lifesaver sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep an eye out for wild mushrooms.//They can be a lifesaver sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I always found comfort in the company of animals.//<portrait=happy>They don’t judge, they don’t ask questions. They just are.
Text.LocalizedString: I always found comfort in the company of animals.//<portrait=happy>They don’t judge, they don’t ask questions. They just are.

Text.SourceString: Don’t get me wrong, art’s great and all, if you’re into that kind of thing.//I should stick to what I know.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get me wrong, art’s great and all, if you’re into that kind of thing.//I should stick to what I know.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think Bonbon can grow any bigger. He’s maxed out.//<portrait=happy>Bonbon’s a pint-sized pup.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think Bonbon can grow any bigger. He’s maxed out.//<portrait=happy>Bonbon’s a pint-sized pup.

Text.SourceString: Gotta take out the trash before it becomes its own ecosystem.//<portrait=annoyed>Here’s hoping I remember to do it before the smell knocks me out tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta take out the trash before it becomes its own ecosystem.//<portrait=annoyed>Here’s hoping I remember to do it before the smell knocks me out tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Every night, I tell my niece good night, and she always hollers back, “Good night!”//<portrait=sad>But pretty soon, she’ll be all grown up and off to <Italic>uni</>. Can’t believe how fast time flies.
Text.LocalizedString: Every night, I tell my niece good night, and she always hollers back, “Good night!”//<portrait=sad>But pretty soon, she’ll be all grown up and off to <Italic>uni</>. Can’t believe how fast time flies.

Text.SourceString: Gonna miss that little bugger.
Text.LocalizedString: Gonna miss that little bugger.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NpcName>Jack</> experiments with different recipes, but let’s just say not all of them are a success.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NpcName>Jack</> experiments with different recipes, but let’s just say not all of them are a success.

Text.SourceString: Accepting his dinner invites is a game of Russian roulette. You never know what you’re signing up for.//Exciting, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Accepting his dinner invites is a game of Russian roulette. You never know what you’re signing up for.//Exciting, though.

Text.SourceString: I prefer simple, hearty meals like tomato soup, smoked salmon, hot cocoa… Does that count?
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer simple, hearty meals like tomato soup, smoked salmon, hot cocoa… Does that count?

Text.SourceString: Anyway, things that don’t require a lot of fuss.//Life’s complicated enough as it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, things that don’t require a lot of fuss.//Life’s complicated enough as it is.

Text.SourceString: I’m terrible at picking out gifts.//I never know what to get people.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m terrible at picking out gifts.//I never know what to get people.

Text.SourceString: Music’s not really my thing, but I can appreciate a good beat when I hear one.
Text.LocalizedString: Music’s not really my thing, but I can appreciate a good beat when I hear one.

Text.SourceString: Taking care of animals can be messy work.//You gotta be prepared to get scratched and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Taking care of animals can be messy work.//You gotta be prepared to get scratched and all.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind it one bit. It’s part of the job.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind it one bit. It’s part of the job.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I’ll help my sister and <NpcName>Paul</> with their wildlife shoots.//<portrait=normal>It’s pretty cool getting up close and personal with some of these animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I’ll help my sister and <NpcName>Paul</> with their wildlife shoots.//<portrait=normal>It’s pretty cool getting up close and personal with some of these animals.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne</> and I used to spend hours in the forest behind our house, watching the wildlife.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne</> and I used to spend hours in the forest behind our house, watching the wildlife.

Text.SourceString: We’d track animals, build forts, and just explore.
Text.LocalizedString: We’d track animals, build forts, and just explore.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> got me a husky calendar for my birthday a few years ago. Told her I liked it… And now she gets me the same one every year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> got me a husky calendar for my birthday a few years ago. Told her I liked it… And now she gets me the same one every year.

Text.SourceString: But you know what? I like it every single time.
Text.LocalizedString: But you know what? I like it every single time.

Text.SourceString: I have a small CRT TV in my room, nothing fancy.//I like it. It does its job.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a small CRT TV in my room, nothing fancy.//I like it. It does its job.

Text.SourceString: The wind is nice today.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is nice today.

Text.SourceString: Storms can be pretty intense.//But they’re nothing to be worried about. Just be sensible.
Text.LocalizedString: Storms can be pretty intense.//But they’re nothing to be worried about. Just be sensible.

Text.SourceString: If you’re worried, just wear a helmet. It’ll protect your head.//<portrait=happy>You <Italic>would</> look ridiculous, though, yeah.//You should do it.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re worried, just wear a helmet. It’ll protect your head.//<portrait=happy>You <Italic>would</> look ridiculous, though, yeah.//You should do it.

Text.SourceString: When a storm rolls in, I’ll admit I get a little excited.//There’s something exhilarating about being in the midst of nature’s fury.
Text.LocalizedString: When a storm rolls in, I’ll admit I get a little excited.//There’s something exhilarating about being in the midst of nature’s fury.
